 
//Why Inner Class Can Access balance Directly? 
Because internally Java does something like: //

class InterestCalculator { 
 
    BankAccount outerReference; 
 
    InterestCalculator(BankAccount ref) { 
        outerReference = ref; 
    } 
 
    double calculateInterest(double rate) { 
        return (outerReference.balance * rate) / 100; 
    } 
} 
 
//But Java hides this from us. 
So when we write: 
account.new InterestCalculator(); 
Java internally passes: account as hidden parameter. 
That is why it works.//
